# Trivy Ignore File - CVE Suppression Rules
# This file allows you to intentionally ignore known CVEs
# Use only after proper risk assessment and approval from security team
# Format: CVE-YYYY-NNNNN

# Example (DO NOT USE for this demo - these should be FIXED, not ignored):
# CVE-2018-1000656
# CVE-2018-18074
# CVE-2018-20225

# For this vulnerable-app demo, we intentionally DO NOT ignore CVEs
# because the goal is to demonstrate the scanning and remediation workflow.
# In production, we would:
# 1. Fix vulnerable dependencies first
# 2. Only ignore CVEs after proper risk assessment
# 3. Track ignored CVEs with business justification
# 4. Set remediation dates for future fixes

